{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_012sifLFuwCjQkp5bn3c12x6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→PRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\n     2→PROJECT: PrizmClaw\n     3→LANG: JavaScript (ESM), Node.js 22\n     4→DESCRIPTION: Telegram → AI CLI bridge with web admin panel; bidirectional sync, pipeline orchestration\n     5→ENTRY: src/index.js\n     6→TEST_CMD: node --test tests/**/*.test.js\n     7→\n     8→MODULE_INDEX:\n     9→- src -> .prizm-docs/src/\n    10→- src/adapters -> .prizm-docs/src/adapters.prizm\n    11→- src/bot -> .prizm-docs/src/bot.prizm\n    12→- src/http -> .prizm-docs/src/http.prizm\n    13→- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/src/pipeline-infra.prizm\n    14→- src/routes -> .prizm-docs/src/routes.prizm\n    15→- src/security -> .prizm-docs/src/security.prizm\n    16→- src/services -> .prizm-docs/src/services.prizm\n    17→- src/utils -> .prizm-docs/src/utils.prizm\n    18→- public -> (static web panel assets — no L1 doc)\n    19→\n    20→RULES:\n    21→- All chat messages route through messageRouter.processMessage() — never call executeAiCli directly for chat\n    22→- Session keys: bound sessions use telegram:{chatId}, unbound web sessions use web:{sessionId}\n    23→- Safe-to-modify config keys: LOG_LEVEL, REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS, AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_MS, MAX_PROMPT_CHARS, MAX_HISTORY_TURNS, SYSTEM_MONITOR_INTERVAL_MS, SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS, TASK_DEBOUNCE_MS\n    24→- ANSI stripping happens in onAssistantChunk hook via ansiProcessChunk() — never strip in final reply path\n    25→- Web panel CSS z-index hierarchy: .app-header=10, command-dropdown=100, lightbox=200, toast=300; details in CLAUDE.md\n    26→- Web panel CSS modifier pattern: .status/.message/.output-box/.toast use modifier classes for state (connected/error/exit-error/success/info); dark mode overrides hardcoded light-palette values; details in CLAUDE.md\n    27→- Dark mode via @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) in styles.css; :root color-scheme is `light dark`; hardcoded #fff backgrounds overridden to var(--panel)\n    28→- CSS breakpoints: 900px collapses grids; 600px mobile layout (flex-wrap header, full-width buttons, reduced padding)\n    29→- Toast: showToast(msg, type) in public/js/main.js; type='success'|'error'|'info'; auto-dismisses 3s + 300ms fade-out animation\n    30→- Lightbox: openLightbox(src)/closeLightbox() in public/js/main.js; close on backdrop click (event.target !== img) or Esc keydown\n    31→- Spinner: setBusy(busy, text, activeBtn?) in public/js/main.js; adds .loading to activeBtn when busy; removes from all buttons when idle; .btn.loading uses ::before pseudo-element with color: transparent on button text\n    32→\n    33→UPDATED: 2026-03-23\n    34→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"567399a5-ce12-4e35-a2f8-9c267f1a7eb9","uuid":"858e362d-2677-4dac-8f04-1b61723fda50","timestamp":"2026-03-23T00:55:08.528Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizm-docs/root.prizm","content":"PRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\nPROJECT: PrizmClaw\nLANG: JavaScript (ESM), Node.js 22\nDESCRIPTION: Telegram → AI CLI bridge with web admin panel; bidirectional sync, pipeline orchestration\nENTRY: src/index.js\nTEST_CMD: node --test tests/**/*.test.js\n\nMODULE_INDEX:\n- src -> .prizm-docs/src/\n- src/adapters -> .prizm-docs/src/adapters.prizm\n- src/bot -> .prizm-docs/src/bot.prizm\n- src/http -> .prizm-docs/src/http.prizm\n- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/src/pipeline-infra.prizm\n- src/routes -> .prizm-docs/src/routes.prizm\n- src/security -> .prizm-docs/src/security.prizm\n- src/services -> .prizm-docs/src/services.prizm\n- src/utils